		<h3>Fun Facts and Inventions!</h3>
		<div id="funfacts">
			<p>Blaise Pascal was born on June 19th, 1623 in Clermont, France.</p>
			<p>His mother died when he was three years old, so he was educated by his 
				father.</p>
			<p>He presented his work on projective geometry at the age of sixteen.</p>
			<p>The famous thinker Descartes initially thought Pascal's father wrote 
				the thesis on geometry Pascal published.</p>
			<p>Pascal's triangle, a model for binomial coefficients, is named after 
				him.</p>
			<p>He invented the calculator, the syringe, and the hydraulic press.</p>
			<p>He had a religious vision that changed his intellectually pursuits 
				towards religion</p>
			<p>His religious views included that suffering was a necessary part of 
				life to experience true joy and pleasure.</p>
			<p>He had a profound impact on probability and game theory using 
				mathematical analysis.</p>
			<p>He died in Paris on August 18th, 1662 at the age of 39 from a stomach 
				related illness, but had suffered from poor health most of his life</p>
		</div><!--end of funfacts div-->
